Robot Defense

by: Pranav Bantval

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I decided to make this game because I used to play a similar game and wanted to add a different aspect to it. This game also seemed very fun to make and I thought it was the best idea I had.

2. What I Learned

I learned that I made my game too hard from testers. The instructions were clear and the game was good, but it was too hard to win. I also received feedback saying that I should add sounds or music to it.

3. Architecture of My Game

The different parts of my game are the starter class, game panel, object manager, and object classes. The game panel works with the starter class to start the game. It also draws the background. The object manager performs all interactions between objects. It works with the game panel to create all of the objects.

4. Technical Implementation

I am very proud of implementing my money system into my game. I wanted money to come and go from a few different areas. Money would be added over time and from killing enemies. It would be removed for buying robots to help you fight.

5. Most Challenging Part

The most challenging part of this project was debugging it. It was very hard to concentrate on the source of the error when there is several classes with hundreds of lines. Often times an error would appear in one class, but was caused from another class. I overcame this by looking carefully at what the problem was and where all the possible sources could be.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

I would like to add music and more characters, enemies, and levels to my game. I would improve it by adding all of those.
